Welcome Bradley Jimerson<br>
Cante Tinza  (Brave Heart) of the Allegany Indian Reservation. <br><br>
I am Cetan (Sparrowhawk). I am not indian, but I carried the 60 in Nam for 10 months, we are brothers in arms. I served in the Republic of Vietnam, June 67 - July 68, USMC 1st Marine Division, 3/7, India Company 1st platoon.<br><br>
I have heard of Point Man Ministries and I am grateful for your ministry. My indian bother, MTF visits here often, I think he's out in his back forties trying on war bonnets.  <br><br>
Welcome home, you are here among those that were proud to have served. We have all suffered for the shame of our country but we stand by her side. We have done only that which was required of us. We stand together.<br><br>

